      nfr: ["No workflow loss; duplicate delivery is harmless; every accepted saga becomes terminal or explicitly operator-actionable.", "Workflow engine sustains 10k starts/s and 500k events/s with 99.99% state-read availability and bounded decision latency.", "One slow domain, tenant, SKU, provider, or region cannot exhaust all workflow workers."],
      capacity: ["10k sagas/s × 35 events × 1.4 KB is 490 MB/s logical history before replicas/indexes.", "A 15-minute payment outage can accumulate 9M waiting sagas; waiting state must be durable and non-thread-blocking.", "30 days × 864M sagas/day is unrealistic at full hot history; compact terminal histories and tier archival aggressively."],
