      model: ["Saga stores business key, definition version, state/version, deadline, commit point, and current exception; Step stores command/result/attempt/timer/compensation.", "DomainOperationInbox deduplicates commandId and stores original outcome; outbox publishes it atomically with domain mutation.", "WorkflowAudit records code/config version, actor, manual action, and before/after state; archived history retains checksums and business evidence."],
      architecture: ["A durable workflow engine owns control flow and timers; domain services own all business state and answer idempotent commands through local outboxes.", "Kafka provides buffered integration and reply streams; workflow task queues are partitioned/bulkheaded by market/domain/priority.", "A separate operations plane indexes workflow summaries and supports safe, audited remediation without editing database rows."],
      components: ["Orchestrator decides sequence/deadline/compensation; activity adapters translate commands; domains enforce invariants and idempotency.", "Timer service persists waits; workflow version router binds in-flight sagas to compatible definitions; operations service owns intervention.", "Reconciliation independently queries domain truth so an engine/history bug cannot become the only account of business state."],
      flows: ["Start → durable saga plus Order=PENDING → reserve inventory → fraud/payment → move the order to CONFIRMED → apply capture policy → fulfillment events.", "Pre-commit failure compensates completed reversible steps in reverse dependency order; post-commit failure uses forward recovery and explicit exception states.", "Timeout produces UNKNOWN, then query/reconcile before repeat; a late outcome is applied if legal or launches a compensating branch."],
