      architecture: ["A home-region profile owner enforces versions and field-level policy; sensitive values sit in a separately controlled PII vault.", "Outbox events carry opaque refs/change classes; registered domains build minimal projections and expose applied-version receipts.", "A privacy workflow registry discovers consumers, sends export/erase commands, gathers attestations, and reports unresolved data."],
      components: ["IAM authenticates accounts; profile owns customer attributes; consent ledger owns legal preference history; PII vault owns encryption/access.", "Identity resolution proposes links/merges but high-risk merges require evidence/review; policy engine filters fields by purpose.", "Privacy orchestrator owns subject requests, deadlines, consumer registry, evidence, and exceptions."],
      flows: ["Authorized patch → validate purpose/source/version → encrypt/tokenize fields → commit profile/outbox → invalidate scoped caches/projections.", "Consent revoke → append decision → priority suppression stream → notification/recommendation enforcement → consumer receipts/reconciliation.", "Erasure request → identity verification → legal-hold classification → domain commands → tombstone/key destruction where allowed → completion report."],
      storage: ["PostgreSQL fits consent, identity links, audit, and policy; DynamoDB/document storage scales profile reads by customerRef.", "Use KMS envelope encryption and separate PII vault, Kafka for sanitized changes, S3 for encrypted export/audit artifacts with expiry."],
